APux2.jpg", "height": 607}], "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 161, "created": 1783838678000, "id": "2076196013597937918", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1870853024798715904/f7G0cKa9_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Basil the Great", "username": "BasilTheGreat"}, "content": "Bluesky put an \"intolerance\" label on a post disagreeing with paedophilia", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 7316}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ATBqfE2wy", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 36, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8725560, "raw_content": "Lynch is a MAGA-aligned businessman from Greenville, South Carolina, who challenged incumbent Lindsey Graham in the 2026 Republican U.S. Senate primary.  Positioning himself as an \"America First\" conservative, Lynch  criticized Graham as a \"RINO\" (Republican In Name Only) and a \"warmonger,\" arguing the senator was insufficiently loyal to President Donald Trump. \r\n\r\nLynch, owner of Jeff Lynch Appliance Center, self-funded millions into his campaign, including a personal commitment of up to $5 million.  Despite polling data suggesting a competitive race among informed voters, he lost the June 9, 2026 primary, where Graham secured 57% of the vote to avoid a runoff.  Trump actively supported Graham, publicly dismissing Lynch as a \"lunatic.\" \r\n\r\nFollowing Graham's death on July 12, 2026, Lynch indicated he is considering another run for the seat in the upcoming special election.  His platform emphasized border security, anti-interventionist foreign policy, and Christian values. ", "author": "Bullet3250", "created": 1783890528070, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Bullet3250", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "previ